    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix socket resource leak in UE standalone mode\n\n### Summary\nWhen running in standalone mode, the UE application creates UDP sockets for communication but fails to close them properly during shutdown. This leads to socket file descriptor leaks that accumulate over multiple runs or long-running sessions.\n\nThe issue occurs downstream of RAR handling when `nrue_init_standalone_socket()` is called but the corresponding cleanup is never performed. The sockets remain open until the process terminates, preventing proper resource cleanup.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/NR_UE_PHY_INTERFACE/NR_IF_Module.c`: Added `nrue_cleanup_standalone_socket()` function to properly close tx/rx sockets\n- `openair2/NR_UE_PHY_INTERFACE/NR_IF_Module.h`: Added function declaration for cleanup function  \n- `executables/nr-uesoftmodem.c`: Integrated socket cleanup into exit handler\n\n### Reproduction\nTo reproduce this issue:\n1. Run UE in standalone mode with `--standalone` flag\n2. Let the application run for extended period or perform multiple connection cycles\n3. Monitor file descriptor usage with `lsof -p <pid>` or `ls -l /proc/<pid>/fd/`\n4. Observe that UDP socket file descriptors accumulate over time without being released\n\nThe leaked sockets can eventually lead to \"too many open files\" errors and degraded system performance.\n"
}